x4freetext: Vol.8, Revision 1, part A and part B.
"Supplemental neutron-induced interactions :
graphical, experimental data."
Number 704 (61) - for this article (NP,47,1,157,1963).
Data are given in Tables.
200-kV Cockcroft-Walton accelerator.
T(D,N)ALPHA from tritiated zirconium target.
Deuterons energy 170 keV.Neutron emission from target
varied from 1.E+7 to 1.E+8 n/sec.
Activation.
Sample sandwiched scintillator as a block of
target foils and plastic scintillator.
Plastic scintillator plates of 1 mm thick,
7.5 mm * 28 mm in area.
CsI crystal mounted on photomultiplier Dumont
6292  - for associated alpha-particles detection.
-Associated alpha particle counting from  T(d,n)ALPHA
reaction at angle 90 deg. to the beam.
Gammas.
Electrons.
Decay curves were analyzed. Decay schemes of
K.Way+,Nuclear Data sheets, were used.
Analysis of decay curve was described in Appendix I
of reference.
Approved by the author.
A.P.T. Japan code changed to JPN
M.M.Dates were corrected for 4-digits year.
Free text was corrected to be "human-readable".
BIB information was added.
"2JPNKON" was added in FACILITY line.
Spin and detection efficiency are added in DECAY-DATA
lines from Table 1 of reference.
Method of least square.
